        "sentiment analysis  can be done using three Python libraries â€” VADER, AFINN, and TextBlob. It compares how each tool interprets emotions in short sentences. VADER is best suited for social media texts, AFINN assigns numeric scores to words, and TextBlob analyzes polarity and subjectivity based on grammar. The results show how different methods handle tone, negations, and emotional intensity in language. This helps understand the strengths of each sentiment analysis approach."
